# Fixed rental roles (product decision)

Do **not** build per-company custom roles or a customer-facing permission matrix.

## Roles (only)

`owner` | `admin` | `operations` | `finance` | `viewer`

Plus **subcompany scope** (`all` / selected) for non-owner/admin members.

## Capability mapping (use `can()` from `@/lib/auth/rental-permissions`)

| Capability | Roles |
|------------|--------|
| `staff.manage` / `settings.manage` / `onboarding.manage` / `contract.change` | owner, admin |
| `fleet.write` / `fleet_tracking.manage` / `subcompany.write` / `maintenance.write` | owner, admin, operations |
| `fleet.delete` | owner, admin |
| `billing.pay` | owner, admin, finance |
| `maintenance.read` | owner, admin, operations, finance, viewer |
| `rentals.read` | owner, admin, operations, finance, viewer |
| `rentals.write` | owner, admin, operations |

When adding modules (claims, customer payments), map them onto these fixed roles — do not invent DIY company roles unless several paying customers block deals without them.

## Implementation

- Prefer `can(profile, "fleet.write")` over scattered `membership_role === …` checks.
- Keep Postgres RLS aligned with the same fixed-role sets.
- Never expose SmartCar Tracker / third-party “roles” as a substitute for company membership roles.
